This paper is about dialogue breakdown detection, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The use of decision tree-based and LSTM-based models suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of ensembles also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of statistical learning (cs.SD) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
